BFN 

  [Text] Four Afghan jihadi groups have called for an 
immediate and unconditional cease-fire among all the conflicting 
factions in Afghanistan. The Central News Unit reports from 
Islamabad that following their meeting in Islamabad, Mojaddedi, 
leader of the National Salvation Party; Mohammadi, leader of the 
Islamic Revolution Movement; Mohseni, leader of the Islamic 
Movement; and Gilani, leader of the National Movement, called 
for the Leadership Council to convene to examine Afghanistan's 
future rule. 
  Afghan President Rabbani's presidential term expires today. 

